</paragraph>
<paragraph id="496CB171B083343F3290B7FCBAF11D5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="2FB88515BE3DD7E74022F12D1AB2A733" authorityName="Ward &amp; Boudinot" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus (Myrmamblys) bellus subsp. leucodiscus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bellus" status="stat. rev." subGenus="Myrmamblys" subSpecies="leucodiscus">Camponotus (Myrmamblys) bellus leucodiscus</taxonomicName>
; Emery, 1925: 138. Placement in 
<taxonomicName id="B8D2895BC874A6E82F4EF7EAE8E5F3CC" authority="" authorityName="Ward &amp; Boudinot" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus (Myrmamblys)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="stat. rev." subGenus="Myrmamblys">Camponotus (Myrmamblys)</taxonomicName>
and subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="B62437DB8734256157153DCE1944D2E8" authorityName="Ward &amp; Boudinot" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ca. bellus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus" status="stat. rev.">Ca. bellus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C99858AAB7786E85C2AB2479047F8559" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" type="">
<paragraph id="9B72D598657750B9B884C9048F3738EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">
Workers associated with 
<taxonomicName id="5F00F46A36EB8088A233F6D0B9A67379" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ca. leucodiscus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucodiscus">
<emphasis id="F2230D957E5BAC044DD45535ECD0E328" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Ca. leucodiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(i.e., matching the striking black and white color pattern on the gaster of the holotype queen) lack the matte integument and pilosity of 
<taxonomicName id="5A92EE94E6D397BCA7016F5A6BEE8D29" authorityName="Ward &amp; Boudinot" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ca. bellus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis id="556543D790FEEDB936DCDFE7DC7123F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Ca. bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and are instead shiny and with sparse pilosity, as described above for 
<taxonomicName id="D741E49B932A2B104AB768BD4D02F4CE" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ca. adustus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adustus">
<emphasis id="95CBA4BE09C5D239CFEB5CBE91D20FFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Ca. adustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They apparently differ from workers of 
<taxonomicName id="0A8A193ABB7787E65CBADA7CEA742B7E" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ca. adustus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adustus">
<emphasis id="F8B947750E3BD2E33F5E3E6831ADEA57" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Ca. adustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer, lower petiole and by the color pattern on the gaster. Both taxa that are here elevated to species are part of a larger assemblage of ants in the 
<taxonomicName id="FA08EB7ED775708FFD5E7DE0E12E799E" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ca." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ca. reticulatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatus">
<emphasis id="FEE61642CC0EA0D3F593E5169DA129F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Ca. reticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group that need comprehensive taxonomic study.
</paragraph>
